## Vercel Speed Insights Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the X-Pand project.

### Changes Made:

#### 1. Package Installation
- **Installed**: `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Location**: Added to dependencies in `package.json`

#### 2. Configuration
- **File Modified**: `frontend/src/App.tsx`
- **Import Added**: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react'`
- **Component Placement**: Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<BrowserRouter>` wrapper, after the `<AppProvider>` component
  
  This placement ensures Speed Insights tracks all route changes and page views across the entire application.

#### 3. Files Updated:
- `frontend/package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights to dependencies
- `frontend/package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component

### Implementation Details:

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (retrieved from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I:

1. Used npm to install the latest version of @vercel/speed-insights
2. Imported the React-specific SpeedInsights component from '@vercel/speed-insights/react'
3. Placed the component at the root level of the app (in App.tsx) to ensure it captures metrics from all pages
4. Maintained the existing code structure without any breaking changes

### Verification:

✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing linting issues in codebase are pre-existing)
✅ Package-lock.json updated correctly
✅ All dependencies installed without vulnerabilities

### Next Steps:

To start collecting performance metrics:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
3. Once deployed, Speed Insights will automatically begin collecting Real Experience Score (RES) and Web Vitals data from real user sessions

### Notes:

- The SpeedInsights component is a lightweight wrapper that loads the tracking script asynchronously
- No additional configuration is required for this React + Vite setup
- The component will only activate when deployed on Vercel's platform
- Local development builds will not send analytics data
